# Settings Pattern

## Hub

One settings shell with tabs (business, branches, users, features, integrations, audit…). Avoid scattering equivalent screens without redirects.

## Rules

- Tab content loads only what it needs
- Mutations permission-gated on server
- `revalidatePath` the settings route after saves
- Success/error toasts
- Dangerous settings need confirm + clear copy of impact

## Users / roles

Manage users inside settings when that is the product convention; keep standalone `/users` as redirect if legacy links exist.

## Feature flags

Toggle via server actions; never trust client-only flags for security boundaries.
